SIMPLE: hematoidin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hematoidin
<hw>Hem`a*toid"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>A crystalline or amorphous pigment, free from iron,
formed from hematin in old blood stains, and in old hemorrhages in the
body. It resembles bilirubin. When present in the corpora lutea it is
called <altname>haemolutein</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hematology</ent>⟦br⟧
